ZCZC EE39
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 272300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS FORMING TO
THE N OF THE UK WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE OVER
FRANCE. THE HIGH PRESSURE SINKS SEWARDS OVERNIGHT AND
THROUGH THURSDAY AS THE LOW IS FCST TO TRACK E. ON FRIDAY
A LARGE DEEP LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IF FCST TO SPREAD IN FM
THE ATLANTIC LYING ACROSS N ROCKALL AT MIDDAY FRIDAY. IT
IS THEN LIKELY TO TRACK E/NE ACROSS NERN SCOTLAND INTO
THE N SEA. ANOTHER LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO FOLLOW A
SIMILAR TRACK LATER ON SATURDAY. STRG WINDS ACROSS THE N
INITIALLY WILL EASE ON WEDNESDAY NIGHT. LATER ON
THURSDAY GALES ARE EXP TO SPREAD E ACROSS THE N OF NITON.
SEV GALES OR STORM FORCE WINDS ARE POSS FOR A TIME IN THE
NW ON FRIDAY BEFORE WINDS MOD LATER. FURTHER GALES ARE
LIKELY ACROSS THE NW OF THE REGION ON SATURDAY
